text: The green-cheeked parakeet (binomial name Pyrrhura molinae) or green-cheeked conure is a small parrot of the Pyrrhura genus. The term conure is often used for this parrot and its relatives in aviculture. It is native to the forests of South America. ==References== Category:Parakeets Category:Birds of South America
title: Green-cheeked parakeet
